<name>SUSPENSION</name>
<ttl id="1002I_S000K_7A80A_T004O" variety="T004O">
<name>FRONT UPPER SUSPENSION ARM</name>
<para id="RM0000010OK00JX" category="G" type-id="3001K" name-id="SP077-14" from="201202">
<name>INSPECTION</name>
<subpara id="RM0000010OK00JX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM0000010OK00JX_01_0001" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001K300000">
<ptxt>INSPECT FRONT UPPER SUSPENSION ARM ASSEMBLY LH</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="F049920E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>As shown in the illustration, move the ball joint stud back and forth 5 times before installing the nut.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a torque wrench, turn the nut continuously at a rate of 2 to 4 seconds per turn and take the torque reading on the fifth turn.</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem>
<t-value1>0.98 to 4.5</t-value1>
<t-value2>10 to 46</t-value2>
<t-value4>9 to 40</t-value4>
<ptxt> or less</ptxt>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check for any cracks and grease leaks on the ball joint dust cover.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
